article.headline: Austin Peay 91, New Orleans 73
article.story: LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Maurice Hampton scored a career-high 27 points as Austin Peay snapped a six-game losing streak with a 91-73 win over New Orleans in the second game of the Billy Minardi Classic on Tuesday night. Anthony Davis added 22 points and Hampton added four steals and two assist for the Governors (2-6), who will play No. 18 Louisville in the championship of the four-team tournament on Wednesday. The Cardinals defeated IUPUI 80-60 earlier Tuesday. Bo McCalebb scored 28 to lead the Privateers (3-6), who've lost three in a row. Hampton sank a 3-pointer with 7:19 left in the first half to break a 22-22 tie and start a 22-7 Austin Peay run. The Governors led 53-37 at the break after going 21 of 39 from the field (54 percent) and 7 of 10 from 3-point range in the opening half. New Orleans scored the first two baskets of the second half, but Austin Peay answered with a 9-2 spurt and never lost control. Austin Peay will play Louisville for the third straight season. The Cardinals won 80-63 last year in Freedom Hall and 86-64 in the first round of the 2003 NCAA tournament. The Minardi Classic is named after Pitino's brother-in-law, who died in the Sept. 11, 2001 attack on the World Trade Center.
